- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper is about training chatbots using natural language data. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper uses Deep Reinforcement Learning (DRL) agents to train the chatbots. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper uses clustering and reward functions to address the challenges of training chatbots. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is relevant as the paper uses neural networks for sentence embeddings. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the implementation of the chatbot training system.
